race.comment: Looks another good race for REGAL ZEUS (6) who is flying. He dropped back to 1400m here last time out and was ridden aggressively in front to use his stamina and hold off all challengers. Back out to a mile now suits even better and while this is harder, he meets a few off breaks that may lack a bit of fitness. Expect Mott to pour the pressure on from the 600m and prove very tough to get past. RISE AT DAWN (5) is off a 56 day let up. He hasn't managed a win this time in but has been close up in some strong races and he does go very well fresh. He'll pair off with REGAL ZEUS and fight it out. LIGHT INFANTRY MAN (1) resumes. He's the class of the field and 1600m is a good kick off point, just whether the tactics are to be negative from the gate is the query. HOLYMANZ (7) is going well and draws to stalk the leading pair. AIR ASSAULT (8) resumes off a short break with the ability to figure at his best.
